// RPi Camera SetUp
// HPH Knowledgebase -RasPi
// Fluvio L. Lobo Fenoglietto

// Follow this guide to learn how to install the Raspberry Pi camera module

1.0- Ensure the Raspberry Pi Board is up-to-date using the following commands

WARNING! This may take a while!

> sudo apt-get update
> sudo apt-get upgrade

2.0- Access the board's configuration settings through the following command...

> sudo raspi-config

3.0- Within the configuration window:

3.1- Navigate to "Camera"
3.2- Select "Enable"
3.3- Select "Finish" and reboot

4.0- After the reboot, turn the board off, connect the camera and turn the system on again

// References

> https://www.raspberrypi.org/blog/camera-board-available-for-sale/